bitfield.description: Used to distinguish between old scheme and current. Spare bit to encode future schemes
Indicating a software compatible module family. If there is no level of software compatibility a new ID should be assigned.
RTL Version. (R as described in PDR 9.3.2) Must be easily ECO'able or controlled during fabrication. Ideally through a top level metal mask or efuse. Start with 0 for PSC1.0, 1 for PSC2.0
Major Revision.
Indicates a Special Version for a particular device. Consequence of use may avoid use of standard CSL/Drivers. 0 if non-custom
Minor Revision Must be easily ECO'able or controlled during fabrication. Ideally through a top level metal mask or efuse. Start with 0.
Evaluate PSC interrupt 0: Write of 0 has no effect 1: Write of 1 re-evaluate the combined PSC interrupt PSC_ALLINT

Clears the interrupt status bits set in the corresponding module error pending register 1 (mod 33) (MERRPR1) and the module status 33 register (MDSTAT33). This pertains to module 33.
